01:02:21,933 --> 01:02:25,800
[If the pledge of this equality]

912
01:02:25,833 --> 01:02:29,567
[We could conquer with strong arm]

913
01:02:29,006 --> 01:02:32,873
[In thy bosom,]
[O freedom]

914
01:02:33,005 --> 01:02:36,372
[Our chest defy death itself!]

915
01:02:36,009 --> 01:02:37,942
[O beloved,]
[Idolized homeland]

916
01:02:38,867 --> 01:02:41,233
[Hail, hail]

917
01:02:41,267 --> 01:02:43,275
[Brazil, an intense dream, a vivid ray]

918
01:02:44,001 --> 01:02:47,534
[Of love and hope descends to earth]

919
01:02:47,667 --> 01:02:51,333
[If in thy comely,]
[Smiling and limpid sky]

920
01:02:51,367 --> 01:02:54,933
[The image of the Southern Cross blazes]

921
01:02:54,967 --> 01:02:59,033
[Giant by thine own nature]

922
01:02:59,067 --> 01:03:02,074
[Thou art beautiful, thou art strong,]
[An impavid colossus]

923
01:03:02,008 --> 01:03:05,375
[And thy future mirrors thy greatness]

924
01:03:06,002 --> 01:03:07,835
[Adored Land]

925
01:03:08,067 --> 01:03:09,800
[Amongst a thousand others]
[Art thou, Brazil]

926
01:03:09,833 --> 01:03:11,700
[O beloved homeland]

927
01:03:11,733 --> 01:03:12,900
[Of the sons of this ground]

928
01:03:12,933 --> 01:03:15,867
[Thou art kind mother,]
[Beloved homeland]

929
01:03:15,009 --> 01:03:16,376
[Brazil!]

930
01:03:28,007 --> 01:03:29,940
[In the democratic game,]

931
01:03:31,833 --> 01:03:34,835
[the winner could become the loser]
[in the next 5 minutes,]

932
01:03:35,067 --> 01:03:37,068
[or maybe nobody wins anything.]

933
01:03:37,733 --> 01:03:39,739
Because the conflicts
are bigger than the solutions.

934
01:03:40,733 --> 01:03:45,735
But I believe that,
in a very peculiar way,

935
01:03:46,633 --> 01:03:53,200
[it could be a good change if we started]
[complaining about what’s wrong.]

936
01:04:04,033 --> 01:04:06,100
Fuck the World Cup!

937
01:04:17,004 --> 01:04:19,871
[40 million people.]

938
01:04:20,003 --> 01:04:23,636
[We made a lot of progress]
[in the last 20 years,]

939
01:04:23,967 --> 01:04:26,533
[thanks to the past governments,]
[the Brazilian society,]

940
01:04:26,567 --> 01:04:27,575
[the democratic constitution.]

941
01:04:28,004 --> 01:04:30,008
[This didn’t just magically happen.]

942
01:04:30,833 --> 01:04:33,967
[We’ve been taking]
[more and more Brazilians]

943
01:04:34,333 --> 01:04:37,400
[from extreme poverty conditions.]

944
01:04:37,433 --> 01:04:39,700
[Now, this people want more.]

945
01:04:44,633 --> 01:04:48,636
[There is the dream of a society]
[that goes beyond the consumer market.]

946
01:04:49,033 --> 01:04:52,037
[Today, we can say we have]
[less social disparities,]

947
01:04:53,002 --> 01:04:55,769
[and that reflects]
[on people´s right to consume.]

948
01:04:56,567 --> 01:05:00,933
However, the public schools
still reproduce social disparities.

949
01:05:01,933 --> 01:05:03,936
[The health system still]
[reproduces social disparities…]

950
01:05:09,009 --> 01:05:11,342
Get out of there!
Get the fuck out of there!

951
01:05:36,667 --> 01:05:39,333
[We will resist!]
[We will resist!]

952
01:06:16,367 --> 01:06:18,372
You're discrediting
the popular wisdom

953
01:06:18,009 --> 01:06:25,376
if you think the people mix victory
in sports with political needs.

954
01:06:26,667 --> 01:06:29,600
Even in the specific moment of victory,
they don't mix the two things together.

955
01:06:29,633 --> 01:06:30,642
It doesn’t mean the governments

956
01:06:31,567 --> 01:06:34,400
don’t try to take advantage
of the situation, though.

